                            <comment id="12412538" author="dagw" created="Sat, 20 May 2006 00:54:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it is good to clean up the sources a bit!  Just a couple of&lt;br/&gt;
comments: I am a bit puzzled this formatting change, which I don&apos;t&lt;br/&gt;
think is very common practice in Derby:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
    // get a new session&lt;br/&gt;
    :&lt;br/&gt;
changed to: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while(!closed())&lt;br/&gt;
    {&lt;br/&gt;
        // get a new session&lt;br/&gt;
        :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;etc. If anything, I think the brace should start on the previous line,&lt;br/&gt;
which is used elsewhere in Derby (mostly). Effectively it indents the&lt;br/&gt;
loop body eight spaces, which is expensive, IMHO. There are several&lt;br/&gt;
instances of this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems you have not sanitized the file wrt to tabs as whitespace,&lt;br/&gt;
either, but I know one could argue the diffs would be too extensive.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe the getting rid of the physical tabs is a lost cause.. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I&lt;br/&gt;
just wish they would go away...&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12412623" author="naka" created="Sat, 20 May 2006 13:22:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I modified DDMWriter as next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Move the opening brace ,&quot;{&quot;, to same line of the starting token of the statement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Untabfy all.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If there are no comment, I will modify other files listed as same and submit patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
