                            <comment id="12414010" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 31 May 2006 17:32:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think these changes should be backed out for two reasons:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  1) This is not the right time to reindent so large parts of the&lt;br/&gt;
     code, as it makes merging to the 10.1 branch difficult.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  2) All of DRDAConnThread (which is one of the largest classes in&lt;br/&gt;
     Derby) has been reindented to a style that is not used in any&lt;br/&gt;
     other Derby class (tab width = 8).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we want to reindent large parts of the code, I think we should do&lt;br/&gt;
it sometime after 10.1.3 is released and before the 10.2 branch is&lt;br/&gt;
created, and we should try to use a style that is used elsewhere in&lt;br/&gt;
the code (I prefer tab-free code myself).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12414041" author="naka" created="Wed, 31 May 2006 20:30:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I see ...&lt;br/&gt;
I will back out the patch and suspend release of 10.1.3 .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
